OL,5, Thirteen-year-old Nika Selivanova made 
OL,6, a heart shape with both her hands,     
OL,7, waving goodbye to her best friend Inna 
OL,8, who was pressed up against the glass   
OL,9, partition that divided the entrance    
OL,10, hall of Kherson's train station from   
OL,11, the waiting area.                      
OL,13,FMoments earlier, they'd hugged, tears  
OL,14,Fwelling up in their eyes. Inna had     
OL,15,Fkissed Asia, a tan dachshund dog       
OL,16,Fwrapped up in a warm blanket, carried  
OL,17,Fby Nika in her arms.                   
OL,19,FThe girls didn't know when they might  
OL,20,Fsee each other again.                  
